questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue in a Spring Boot application where a database update is not rolling back after an exception. The code snippet is as follows:

java
@Service
public class TransactionalService {
    public void processOrder(Order order) {
        try {
            saveOrder(order);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            // Error handling
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRED)
    public void saveOrder(Order order) {
        orderRepository.save(order);
        throw new RuntimeException("Force rollback");
    }
}

Despite the `RuntimeException`, the order remains in the database.
